<li><a href="#ch6">Chapter 6: Best Practices for Maximum Success</a></li>
<li><a href="#ch7">Chapter 7: Scaling Link Reclamation From 5 to 50+ Links Per Month</a></li>
<li><a href="#ch8">Chapter 8: Common Mistakes That Kill Reclamation Campaigns</a></li>
<li><a href="#faq">Frequently Asked Questions</a></li>
</ul>
<h2>Chapter 1: What Is Link Reclamation and Why It Works &#123;#ch1&#125;</h2>
<p>Link reclamation is the process of finding and recovering backlinks that once pointed to your site but no longer do. These links may be broken, removed, or never linked in the first place despite a brand mention.</p>
<p>The difference between link reclamation and traditional link building is simple. Traditional link building asks strangers to link to you. Link reclamation asks people who already know you to fix a link they once gave you. The psychological barrier is lower. The success rate is higher. If you are building a new site, our guide on how to <a href="/blog/build-backlinks-for-blog/">build backlinks for your blog</a> covers cold outreach from scratch.</p>
<h3>Link Reclamation vs Traditional Link Building</h3>
